{"type":"message","id":"af6a1c8e","parentId":"988744f1","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:40:34.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"学到了。\n\n这次我该学到的点很明确：\n\n- **装了 Skill ≠ 它在运行**\n- **真正会主动发消息的，很多是 OpenClaw 的 cron job**\n- 以后遇到“这个推送哪来的”，我不能先按“技能 / 脚本 / cron”拍脑袋判断，得先去**定位实际运行源头**\n\n这次你说得对。\n你点名的这条，最后我定位到的不是“某个技能在跑”，而是 OpenClaw 自己的定时任务：\n\n- 文件：`/Users/ling/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json`\n- 任务名：`09:00量化回测队列检查提醒-v2`\n- id：`ffd77541-44ce-46e3-82f4-2c43a3a2f144`\n- 实际跑的脚本：`report_backtest_queue_status.py`\n\n也就是说，**问题核心不是“装了什么技能”**，而是**OpenClaw 调度表里哪条 job 开着**。\n这条我已经按这个思路关掉了。\n\n以后我会按这个顺序处理：\n1. 先定位是 **OpenClaw cron / 系统 crontab / heartbeat / 手工脚本**\n2. 再判断它是不是某个 skill 触发的\n3. 最后才动手停用，避免误判\n\n这次算我被你纠正到位了。\n如果你愿意，我下一步可以把 `jobs.json` 里**目前所有会主动 DM 你的 OpenClaw 定时任务**给你拉一张清单，分成：\n- 正在运行\n- 已关闭\n- 建议保留\n- 建议观察\n\n这样以后就不会再靠猜。"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776562834008}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b016e2f","parentId":"af6a1c8e","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:41:49.276Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-19 09:41:45 GMT+8] Feishu[coding-agent] DM | 张玲 (ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae) [msg:om_x100b5177635db8a4c4e27c32c14d49f]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5177635db8a4c4e27c32c14d49f\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae\",\n  \"sender\": \"张玲\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-04-19 09:41 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"张玲 (ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae\",\n  \"name\": \"张玲\"\n}\n```\n\n我对于现在检查github更新这个定时任务的执行结果很不满意，很多skill我在本地安装了，检查的时候说没有安装；也没说清楚到底哪些值得更新，如果是值得更新的，那就应该自动更新。"}],"timestamp":1776562909268}}
{"type":"message","id":"4316d6f3","parentId":"9b016e2f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:42:12.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Addressing GitHub concerns**\n\nI need to respond to the user about their dissatisfaction with the GitHub update task execution results. First, I should check the relevant scheduled job to see if it needs fixing. I might look into skills like openclaw-workspace, GitHub, or clawhub. It seems clawhub could apply if it’s about updating installed skills. The user’s mention of \"检查github更新这个定时任务的执行结果\" suggests it is related to a GitHub repo update job. I’ll investigate that and may use memory_search since they expressed dissatisfaction.\n\n**Investigating GitHub update task**\n\nThe user is asking about the execution results of the GitHub update scheduled task and mentions issues with locally installed skills being misdetected. I’m considering whether the clawhub skill might apply since it deals with searching, installing, and updating skills. However, the scheduled task seems to be related to the GitHub repo update state. I may need to look into the update checker and possibly inspect local files, although there doesn’t seem to be a specific skill for this. I might skip that if nothing clearly applies.\n\n**Investigating cron job setup**\n\nI need to take action with the tools available to me. It seems that I should investigate the cron job or report related to the \"github_repo_update.\" First, I may check the jobs.json file for that specific job and its source script. The report from today around 09:00 likely holds critical information. I should read through the script or task prompt and consider if adjustments are needed to ensure it detects installed skills and possibly implement an auto-update feature for relevant ones.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b3ac7b405e714490169e432e5fa40819aa959b8c7dc9ff6f2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp5DLvgPagUSg0NQJN97m7xZn4Ahp3c_rTpijdne