{"type":"message","id":"842ae49e","parentId":"7c1637a6","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:46:37.687Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering update processes**\n\nI'm thinking about using the metadata version and origin to detect local modifications, but it's complicated. A simpler solution might be treating files in the .clawhub/origin as managed by ClawHub. We could decide not to auto-update if we detect risks, but that's tricky. The user suggests that auto-updating could be worth it. If I use `clawhub update <slug>`, it may resolve versions safely, but I have to consider the risks of auto-updating in certain cases.\n\n**Evaluating update strategies**\n\nI’m considering implementing a detection system for automatic updates only when the skill has a `.clawhub/origin.json` and matches the local slug without any custom file markers. However, local modifications can't be directly detected. I think I might need to inspect the modification time or compare versions, but even that doesn't seem sufficient. Using `clawhub update <slug>` without `--force` sounds reasonable if it declines on mismatched changes. I could try this manually on a likely up-to-date skill for better insight.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b3ac7b405e714490169e433f5bc98819aaf2e71ee5c60a20c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp5DP8nUusSLho199IYmHayxr9pIO9Rq5XTiwebXSozUgF5Z-rKCeNVVgqP5dG2BjT4iG2w6n0kvtXkbp6UCE5BHTlpdXhBynsP9zSK8_i8Wl4haaRz2au1S2kyRuRsDDd7kpqnteSL0u2Twnqe9DKubqkl_vTbl_5ZcVZLw-m933m-3iJtmKftPMuMGfm2qRwnHNlq2mgLp-xXXncA8Y6BBtL9Y_FkvMtKHIE1aD-8zzaKz-fHdozKPkwDED79cKcODnJWXWXLUiOERiUL-W9gLi-pT6My8LCw4hrqH36mH6Ypfguf4t8Ci93U5nzhK6h8inkX-43TSsQvJ8oCKxoCNhQK7OIjplLEAKMfp9WX91RLf7wYvUIk9K1Yoxk-em_CIY4TsEI828Py0kH9OiBgH4yeGMQEo3AdKlrPFI6fTk8cSTEwBPaoSIFZ0azjRV_pWmThjUeyba8d-1ven4P1SYjawRdFq4OFDySXsASByaiinwnPztnxbgC58l92tP7j3o0-Lvg0itwPyGp0Y4E23OEn4rwcKLGhGCE48U17_0J-Dk6Qnp1nL2uFtNMuMsvIYRiX3lclFk-GVd_Syd5jEmpt2jhFfDN5iKWh1Yhd-r8q7k