m|fc_0b3ac7b405e714490169e435d90c28819a960a230915ee8117","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"~/Library/pnpm/global/5/.pnpm/openclaw@2026.4.10_@emnapi+core@1.9.2_@emnapi+runtime@1.9.2_@napi-rs+canvas@0.1.97_@typ_a90ffd2929abe8f398b8e8e6d84b8ef0/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":217220,"output":630,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":217850,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776563656167,"responseId":"resp_0b3ac7b405e714490169e435cba418819a845c620a3c61358a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"be067a35","parentId":"f6528609","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:54:34.299Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_rXQN8iAsjwWiLv4pkWWR5Khm|fc_0b3ac7b405e714490169e435d90c28819a960a230915ee8117","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: clawhub\ndescription: Use the ClawHub CLI to search, install, update, and publish agent skills from clawhub.com. Use when you need to fetch new skills on the fly, sync installed skills to latest or a specific version, or publish new/updated skill folders with the npm-installed clawhub CLI.\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"clawhub\",\n              \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install ClawHub CLI (npm)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# ClawHub CLI\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g clawhub\n```\n\nAuth (publish)\n\n```bash\nclawhub login\nclawhub whoami\n```\n\nSearch\n\n```bash\nclawhub search \"postgres backups\"\n```\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nclawhub install my-skill\nclawhub install my-skill --version 1.2.3\n```\n\nUpdate (hash-based match + upgrade)\n\n```bash\nclawhub update my-skill\nclawhub update my-skill --version 1.2.3\nclawhub update --all\nclawhub update my-skill --force\nclawhub update --all --no-input --force\n```\n\nList\n\n```bash\nclawhub list\n```\n\nPublish\n\n```bash\nclawhub publish ./my-skill --slug my-skill --name \"My Skill\" --version 1.2.0 --changelog \"Fixes + docs\"\n```\n\nNotes\n\n- Default registry: https://clawhub.com (override with CLAWHUB_REGISTRY or --registry)\n- Default workdir: cwd (falls back to OpenClaw workspace); install dir: ./skills (override with --workdir / --dir / CLAWHUB_WORKDIR)\n- Update command hashes local files, resolves matching version, and upgrades to latest unless --version is set\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776563674283}}
{"type":"message","id":"db09863c","parentId":"be067a35","timestamp":"2026-04-19T01:55:01.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting package updates**\n\nI need to check on the package manager and possibly run a global update for openclaw. It's possible that the openclaw status suggests an update to version 2026.4.15, but it seems the help feature is disabled. I can try running the `openclaw update` command directly. Alternatively, I might consider using `npm i -g openclaw@2026.4.15`, but I need to check if I have the necessary permissions since it's installed globally. I'll look into the current binary path and check the installed version too.\n\n**Considering installation approach**\n\nI'm wondering whether I should run installs in parallel or sequentially to avoid running into rate limits. It might be smart to use clawhub to search for each item first, but I need to be cautious with direct installs since they might fail if the slug is absent. Before installing, I should check where clawhub installs items—likely in the workspace or skills directory. I should also consider updating the cron jobs, but maybe it's not necessary now. It seems like I should commit changes after editing scripts.\n\n**Addressing OpenClaw upgrade concerns**\n\nI’m considering the potential issue of upgrading OpenClaw, wondering if the restart is necessary. It seems manageable, though, since the current agent might keep running despite the package update. I should proceed cautiously, maybe running `openclaw status` after the update to check everything. For cleaning up afterwards, I might need to rerun `skill_update_check` with the auto-update-safe option. I suspect there are about three missing items, and some might get installed in the workspace or skills folders. One built-in skill, `skill-creator`, is already resolved.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b3ac7b405e714490169e435e546bc819a81a58f47ec2f3b3d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_c